With his victory, Sinner became the fourth — and youngest — man to reach the final at all nine Masters 1000 events, joining Novak Djokovic (25y), Rafael Nadal (27y) and Roger Federer (30y). He has now won 27 consecutive matches at this level, a streak that includes titles in Paris last year and Indian Wells, Miami and Monte-Carlo in 2026.

